# Real-provider smoke: drives one chat turn through whatever provider/model
# is currently set as default in ~/.config/zag/config.lua, using the user's
# real ~/.config/zag/auth.json. No --mock flag means the harness leaves
# $HOME alone, so zag picks up the real config the same way it does in a
# normal terminal session.
#
# Probabilistic by design: we don't expect_text the model output (gpt-5.2
# won't say the same words twice). We only assert the welcome banner,
# wait long enough for first-token latency + a short reply, snapshot the
# screen so we can eyeball the artifact, and then /quit cleanly. A
# regression in real-provider plumbing (auth, streaming, SSE parser)
# would either time out at wait_idle or trip wait_exit's crash check.

spawn ./zig-out/bin/zag
wait_text /Welcome to zag/
wait_idle 500ms
send "say hi in three words" <Enter>
wait_idle 20s
snapshot final
send "/quit" <Enter>
wait_exit
